    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:h i_CTRL-U-default` cannot find any help page\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n\ntry\n> :h i_CTRL-U-default\n\nand\n> :h i_ctrl-u-default\n> :h i_cTRL-U-DEFAULT\n> :h i_Ctrl-U-default\n> :h i_ctrl-U-DEFAULT\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe latter can open the help document normally, but the former can't.\n\nSimilarly `i_CTRL-W-default` and `CTRL-L-default` will cause problems, but `CTRL-W_d-default` is normal\n\nActually, I saw these problems when I was looking at the `default-mappings` help page.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.2 and v0.13.0-dev-375+g1e06e95662\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.697, vim has no `i_CTRL-U-default` help page\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwsl/ubuntu24.04.4\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows terminal 1.24.10921.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nlinuxbrew and bin",
